==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unnerve
<hw>Un*nerve"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>nerve</ets>.]</ety> <def>To deprive of nerve,
force, or strength; to weaken; to enfeeble; <as>as, to <ex>unnerve</ex>
the arm</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Unequal match'd, . . . ⟦br⟧
The <qex>unnerved</qex> father falls.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unnest</ent>⟦br⟧
